“0 virtue, where dost thou hide thy-sels? What hideous thing is this which doth eclipse thee? Or is it true that thou wert never but a vain name, and no essential thing? . . . . The duchess replies to Ferdinand's speech by tell- ing him that she is married, though perhaps not to his liking, and that his design concerning her future has been frustrated :—

Alas, your shears do come untimely now To clip the bird's wings that's already flown !
